8:
I did it again! Stella TOLD me to be
more careful, and I let her down!
10:
The Diviners' Commission even
dropped by to thank me for
yesterday. Just what did I do?
14:
I need to ask someone what
happened, but if I do, they'll find out I
don't remember anything. What if
they kick me out of Starview Village?!
23:
Y-yes, I'm perfectly fine! Please don't
kick me out!
35:
I-I mean, never mind me! O-oh
yeah, what's with all the flashy
people around? Is something going
on today?
40:
Huh? Ah, lemme guess... You don't
remember...
45:
This is not the time to be loafing
around, Suzuka! Come here this
instant!
55:
They're holding a New Year's talent
show today.
58:
O-okay... What does that have to do
with me?
72:
And to make things interesting, you
and I turned it into a competition!
75:
This is no mere talent show, Suzuka.
It's a battle between rivals!
93:
There's no way I can get up on that
stage! Help meee!
96:
Uhh... If it's that terrifying, you can
just withdraw...
102: Of course I want to, but...
104:
If drunk me keeps messing up like
this, Stella could kick me out of
Starview Village!
108: Yeah, I don't think she'd do that...
113:
Regardless, I don't want to
disappoint Stella any more than I
already have!
116: Please, Alk, I'm begging you. Help me!
118:
There must be some way to turn
someone like me into a performer
good enough to impress Stella, right?
121:
It may not sound like it, but you're
asking for a lot, you know that?
124:
Hmm... Given the time limit, it's
probably best to make use of your
natural talents and individuality...
133:
We don't have time for questions.
We need to get practicing right
away.
134:
For starters, can you show me all
your ninja equipment?
139:
And that's all for Inaho and the fox
kits! Thank you very much!
141:
Up next is... Ah, our next performer
wishes to remain anonymous... Is
that allowed? Well, whatever! Come
on up, whoever you are!
144: Ah, uh, umm... Yes, th-that's me!
168:
I'm entry number seven! I hope you
enjoy my performance!
174:
I see! She's performing using her
ninja arts!
179:
Oho, good call, Suzuka. I am
impressed!
188:
Yeah, she should give herself more
credit...
193:
I shall admit defeat. You won fair
and square!
196:
That being said, that show of yours
was a real eye-opener! For
something so plain, it sure was
aggressive!
200:
Um, thank you... I think? That doesn't
sound like a compliment!
210:
Ah... Hehe... I'm so glad I did all that
practice.
214:
It feels like a weight has been lifted
off my shoulders.
217:
Hey, she's the one who did that
performance, right?
218:
That was something else, huh? I
think she's a ninja from the East...
224:
Um... Wasn't the whole point of me
changing clothes to hide my identity?
227: Ah... Yeah, now that you mention it...
231:
I just showed off my ninja arts for all
the world to see... My cover's
completely blown!
235:
Well, I don't think you need to worry
about those ninjas anyway.
239:
Indeed. You won't be hearing from
them again.
244:
Why are you two so calm about
this? I'm in deep, deep trouble!
